Some more insight¶

Let's look at a slightly more complex case: car collisions in Seattle

Layers and Maps¶

Layer structure:

Layer(
    source=...,
    style=...,
    legends=[...],
    widgets=[...],
    popup_hover=[...],
    popup_click=[...],
)

Maps allow you to add several layers, select the basemap, set a viewport, and others.

In [6]:
df = pd.read_csv('data/seattle_collisions.csv')
seattle_collisions = gpd.GeoDataFrame(
    df,
    geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(df.longitude, df.latitude),
    crs=4326
)
In [8]:
from cartoframes.viz import Layer
from cartoframes.viz.styles import color_category_style
from cartoframes.viz.widgets import formula_widget, category_widget
from cartoframes.viz.popups import popup_element

Layer(
    seattle_collisions,
    popup_hover=[popup_element('st_coldesc', title='Description')],
    widgets=[
        formula_widget(
            value='pedcount',
            operation='sum',
            title='Pedestrians Involved'
        ),
        formula_widget(
            value='pedcylcount',
            operation='sum',
            title='Cyclists Involved'
        ),
        category_widget(
            'collisiontype',
            title='Collision Type'
        )
    ]
)

A much more complex example¶

In [9]:
df = pd.read_csv('data/maxhi_20190717_72.csv')
max_heat = gpd.GeoDataFrame(
    df,
    geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(df.longitude, df.latitude),
    crs=4326
)
In [11]:
from cartoframes.viz.legends import color_continuous_legend
from cartoframes.viz.styles import color_continuous_style
from cartoframes.viz.widgets import formula_widget, time_series_widget
from cartoframes.viz import Map, basemaps

Map(
    Layer(
        max_heat,
        style=color_continuous_style(
            'value',
            palette=['turquoise', 'yellow', 'red'],
            size=4,
            animate='value'
        ),
        legends=[
            color_continuous_legend(
                title='Max Heat Index for July 20, 2019',
                description='Degrees (F)',
                footer='Issued: 7/17/19 | Source: NOAA Weather Predicition Center'
            )
        ],
        widgets=[
            formula_widget(value='value', operation='max', title='Max Degrees (F)'),
            time_series_widget(value='value', title='Animation by Temperature'),
        ],
    ),
    basemap=basemaps.darkmatter,
    show_info=True,
    viewport={'zoom': 2.5, 'lat': 37.572586, 'lng': -110.638529},
)

Helper Styles - how helpful are they?¶

The most common helper styles don't only set defaults for the map style itself but also for common elements, such as widgets, legends and popups
